{"build_type":"library","description":"Channel B persistent serve loop. Tail-recursively calls serve-portal-region-request-running-helper-writing-reply, which blocks on the request eventfd (fd3), runs one request through the shell and rings the response eventfd (fd4), then loops to wait for the next request. Event-driven (each iteration blocks on fd3), no busy-wait. The gate-aware kernel-root runs this (passing the shell path) so the portal serves requests for the life of the kernel. Additive Channel B; does not touch Channel A.","module_name":"serve-portal-region-requests-running-helper-repeatedly","package_name":"serve-portal-region-requests-running-helper-repeatedly","function_definitions":{"serve-portal-region-requests-running-helper-repeatedly":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"shell_path","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"unused1","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"function_invocation","invocation_name":"serve-portal-region-request-running-helper-writing-reply","invocation_arguments":[{"kind":"var","value":"shell_path"},{"kind":"var","value":"zero"}],"result_assignment_variable":"sv","result_type":"i64"},{"instruction_type":"function_invocation","invocation_name":"serve-portal-region-requests-running-helper-repeatedly","invocation_arguments":[{"kind":"var","value":"shell_path"},{"kind":"var","value":"zero"}],"result_assignment_variable":"r","result_type":"i64"},{"instruction_type":"return_statement","return_payload":{"value":"r"}}]}}}